I&#39;ve been testing an optical link design that replaces a normal microphone. The link consists of a red LED coupled to the sound source (EVP Maker or Linear radio  sweep) and the resultant modulated light is picked up by a photomultiplier tube.  The output of the tube is recorded on a VHS VCR (analog). Here&#39;s a couple examples from the session using EVP maker.

Example one: &quot;Some people being taught, there&#39;s mentors feeling hope&quot;

Example two English or Scottish accent: &quot;Ultimate test, does he pass it?&quot;

Dave
